I told her the name of the order, and the contents, and she refused to give me the order until seeing it on the app. Even after showing her on the app, she still refused until another staff member told her that the order was in fact mine. If this was my neighborhood, this would be my spot! The service was amazing, the girls are all so polite and pleasant. My husband and I randomly stopped in because we saw they had backyard seating and we didn’t need a reservation. It’s a cozy little backyard with seating for small and large groups. Beyond the ambiance and excellent service, the food was amazing. Everything was fresh and tasty, and cooked to perfection. My husband had the grilled pork with papaya salad. It came with jasmine sticky rice in a cute little basket. I had the 1/2 boneless duck with spicy (mildly) basil fried rice. We also had the chicken satay and tamarind duck roll as appetizers. He also had the Caribbean Lover cocktail and it was great. I’ve been to other Thai restaurants that served similar food and the prices were higher. I felt this was really reasonable. I would definitely recommend and return sometime!

This review is for the service received today. The food was excellent as always.  I dine here regularly.  It truly is my go to place for family members b-day, Friday night girls out, quick bite with the hubby and even when I just want some me time, I go alone.  Today we had take out because of social distancing.  My husband and I decided to drive all the way there and pick up because we just missed the place.  Our total came to $46.87 for shrimp basil fried rice, papaya salad and a duck entree with broad noodles.  My husb gave them $50 cash and told them keep the change of $3.13.  Upon almost exiting my husband remembered I had asked for an extra sauce on the side.  He turned around and asked them for the sauce. He was told $1. He went in his pocket and gave them a dollar. He was then told 9¢ more.  He checked his pockets and did not have 9¢.  He told them unfortunately he did not have 9¢.  They told him he can use his card to purchase the $1.09 sauce.  He advised he did not have his card on him.  He was told they could not give him the sauce.  FOR 9¢, you tell a customer that just spent almost $50 and gave you the balance, that you cannot give him a sauce BECAUSE OF 9¢??? My husband was taken aback.  He said "I just spent almost $50 on food and gave you a $3.13 tip for nothing at all and you will deny me sauce for 9¢? Ok then, take the 9¢ out of the tip then".  The person had the nerve to be shocked he was requesting such...and gave him the sauce for $1.  I find it appalling that Born would treat their customers this way over 9¢, when honestly we didn't have to tip them anything, as we were picking up our food. I still can't believe this happened.  OVER NINE CENTS!! 😧 When people are not dining out as much and being very prudent on how and where they're spending their money, Born you really should do a better job at appreciating your loyal customers that are still supporting you during these hard times.

I called anyway, I didn't think they were that serious but they actually appeared to be serious. The man said he would deliver if i put a tip on card, and if I wanted to tip in cash, I would have to go to the restaurant and pick it up myself.  1. Why would a person give tip before seeing/tasting their food or even seeing how the person present themselves? 2. more importantly, out the hundred times we've ordered and tipped, you get rude for the ONE time we didn't?  A tip is given when you go above and beyond for a person, build a connection or if the weather is horrible. If you don't do that then you're an ordinary person. I'm simply just going to pay for the food. These people literally FORCED us to tip them.

Nice place, with even better food. Stumbled on this place while looking for a place with good drinks and good food. I'm glad my friend chose to walk in. I ordered a knockout (drink). It was good, not as strong as I expected it to be. However the appetizers and entre made up for it. We had the rock shrimp. It tasted so good. They present it to you in a martini glass. The shrimp is sitting in a bed of lettuce and a sweet dressing at the bottom. We also had the steamed veg and thai dumplings. Both were very good. The crispy rolls are very good too. It's a thin crispy roll with shrimp, accompanied by a dipping sauce. My friend ordered the duck with Jasmine rice. The duck was delicious! What made it even better was the sauce it came with. Everything that we tried that night was good. Even our bartender Somboon. He made our evening pleasant and fun. If you're ever in the Flatbush/downtown area and looking for a place to enjoy good food and drinks with friends/family, Born Thai Is the place to go!!!

A overwhelmingly pleasurable experience.  We were seated promptly in a tastefully Brooklyn modern interior. The Talking Heads and Beatles played at a nice quiet but audible volume over head.   We started with the Tom Kai vegetable soup.  At first bite this did not blow me away but had the power to keep pulling my spoon back and I was struck with a keen sense of disappointment when it was gone.   The Pad Se Ew was good and flavorful - but standard.  The Masaman on the other had was refreshingly excellent.  It had fresh avocado and chick peas.  Intense mouth filling taste that did not overwhelm but warm - like a nice hug from your fat grandma.  Service was fast and friendly.  My water glass was never more than half empty - which is important to me when eating a spicy meal.  This is my new neighborhood Thai location.
